From: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 31 May 2026
Subject: [PATCH] transcoding/vaapi: do not send level=0 to H264/HEVC encoders

A VAAPI profile whose "level" is left unset stores 0 in the level field
(the class default is only applied to brand-new nodes, not to loaded
profiles). The option-building code guarded only against the "skip"
sentinel (-100), so level=0 was injected into the encoder options.

level 0 is not a valid H264/HEVC level (h264: 10..62, hevc: 30..186), and
the Intel iHD driver rejects it: every frame fails with
VA_STATUS_ERROR_ENCODING_ERROR (code 24) -> "Failed to end picture encode
issue: 24" -> Encode failed: -5. This affected both h264_vaapi and
hevc_vaapi (both emitted level=0), producing audio-only output (and,
before the companion transcode fix, an infinite encode-error loop).

Reproduced and bisected with a standalone ffmpeg run on Intel Apollo Lake
(iHD 24.4.4): the exact tvheadend option set encodes fine except when
"-level 0" is present; "-level 30" or omitting level both succeed.

Fix by only sending an explicit level when it is a real value (> 0). Both
the -100 sentinel and an unset/0 level now mean "let the encoder choose
the level from resolution and bitrate", which is the intended behaviour.

This supersedes the previous 104 patch (max_frame_size=0), which was based
on an incorrect hypothesis and had no effect on the failure.

Suggested-by: Claude Opus 4.8 (Anthropic AI <https://anthropic.com>)
Signed-off-by: Vincent Fortier <th0ma7@gmail.com>

--- src/transcoding/codec/codecs/libs/vaapi.c.orig	2026-05-30 13:35:08.000000000 +0000
+++ src/transcoding/codec/codecs/libs/vaapi.c	2026-05-31 19:30:00.000000000 +0000
@@ -401,8 +401,13 @@
     if (self->async_depth) {
         AV_DICT_SET_INT(LST_VAAPI, opts, "async_depth", self->async_depth, AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
     }
+    // Only send an explicit level when it is a real H264/HEVC level value.
+    // Valid levels are > 0 (h264: 10..62, hevc: 30..186); the "skip" sentinel is
+    // -100 and an unset level field defaults to 0. Both mean "let the encoder pick
+    // the level from resolution/bitrate". Sending level=0 makes the VAAPI driver
+    // fail every frame with VA_STATUS_ERROR_ENCODING_ERROR (24).
     if ((codec == H264 || codec == HEVC) &&
-        self->level != -100) {
+        self->level > 0) {
             AV_DICT_SET_INT(LST_VAAPI, opts, "level", self->level, AV_DICT_DONT_OVERWRITE);
     }
     if (self->qmin) {
